[2] Canada (Ontario)
Date: 19 Mar 2014
Source: Metro News [edited]
http://metronews.ca/news/london/977513/2nd-suspected-case-of-measles-reported-london-health-unit/


The Middlesex-London Health Unit [in Ontario, Canada] is dealing with a 2nd suspected case of measles.

Officials released a list late Wednesday [19 Mar 2014] of London [Canada] businesses visited by the person believed to be carrying the virus. The health unit issued a similar alert Saturday [15 Mar 2014] after confirming a single case of measles.

Ottawa Public Health is investigating a 2nd possible measles case, and Fraser Health is warning of a measles outbreak. Anyone with symptoms, including irritated eyes, a rash, and small white, grey, or blue spots in the mouth should call the health unit or a doctor as soon as possible, officials say.

Measles is spread through the air and is highly contagious, the health unit says. But people who have received 2 doses of the measles vaccine or who have been previously infected or who were born before 1970 are generally safe.

Locations and times of possible exposure are:
- McDonald's (959 Hamilton Rd.): Sat 15 Mar 2014, 2:15 to 6:00 p.m.
- Walmart (White Oaks Mall): Sat 15 Mar 2014, from 7:30 p.m. to after closing
- Best Buy (1080 Wellington Rd.): Sat 15 Mar 2014, from 8:30 p.m. to after closing
- Future Shop (1051 Wellington Rd.): Sat 15 Mar 2014, from 8:45 p.m. to after closing
- SilverCity Theatre (Masonville Place, particularly those attending Need for Speed, 2D movie): Sun 16 Mar 2014, from 8:30 p.m. to closing
- Value Village (4465 Wellington Rd. S.): Tue 18 Mar 2014, and Wed 19 Mar 2014, 7:30 to 10:30 a.m.
- London Health Sciences Centre (Victoria Campus, emergency department): Tue 18 Mar 2014, from 8:30 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
- Tim Hortons (Commissioners and Boler roads): Tue 18 Mar 2014, from 6:00 to 9:00 p.m.

Check the health unit's website for additional details.

