[4] USA (California)
Date: 19 Mar 2014
Source: OC Register [edited]
http://www.ocregister.com/articles/measles-606245-patients-zahn.html


Seven adults and 3 children have been infected with measles, 5 of them after exposure to another measles patient. Seven required hospitalization.

Ten Orange County residents have contracted measles so far this year [2014], with 7 of the patients requiring hospitalization, public health officials said Wednesday [19 Mar 2014].

Three more infections have been confirmed since Friday [14 Mar 2014], correlating with an increase across California.

"It's important to recognize these events as the reason we get our kids vaccinated and the reason we vaccinate ourselves," said Dr. Matt Zahn, the county's medical director for epidemiology.

