[Unfortunately, transmission of measles in healthcare settings is quite common. Measles virus is airborne, remains infectious for a period of hours even after an infectious patient is no longer present, and often goes unrecognized by healthcare providers who have become increasingly unfamiliar with the disease. This results in hazards, particularly for those at increased risk of measles due to factors such as being immunocompromised and pregnancy.

